<section class="section section--surface">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p class="lead">You start with your real situation—savings, income, rent, debts—and {{ site.name }} helps you connect that to a home target, timeline, and the full cash picture (down payment, closing, reserves, and moving).</p>
    </div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li><strong>Create your account</strong> and sign in securely. The iOS app supports email sign-in and other providers configured in the app.</li>
      <li><strong>Set your foundation</strong>—what you’ve saved, what you can save monthly, and how a future housing payment might fit next to rent and debts.</li>
      <li><strong>Shape your target</strong> with a draft home price or a monthly housing budget, then refine with taxes, insurance, and (when applicable) planning estimates like mortgage insurance below 20% down.</li>
      <li><strong>Optionally link accounts</strong> through Plaid so counted balances stay close to reality, or add manual “home fund” amounts if you prefer not to link.</li>
      <li><strong>Follow the roadmap</strong> for bite-sized education and the next best preparation step—without turning everything into one giant form.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Features vary by app version; this page reflects the current product direction in the shipped app.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>What you can plan for</h2>
      <p class="lead">The planner is built around the cash and monthly payment reality of buying—not just a single “down payment” number.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Cash-to-close picture</h3>
        <p class="muted">Down payment, closing costs, post-close reserves, and moving/setup budget roll into a total cash target so savings goals match what closing actually tends to require.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Monthly housing estimate</h3>
        <p class="muted">Principal and interest plus taxes and insurance—and, when your down payment assumption is under 20%, an illustrative conventional-style PMI estimate so monthly totals stay honest for planning.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Home fund allocation</h3>
        <p class="muted">Linked or manual funds can be tagged toward down payment, closing, reserves, or general home savings—including split allocations when one account serves more than one purpose.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Roadmap &amp; learning</h3>
        <p class="muted">Stages break the journey into milestones and modules so preparation, education, and inputs stay tied together instead of scattered across screens.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Market context (where enabled)</h3>
        <p class="muted">The app can incorporate housing-market and benchmark context to help you sanity-check a target—not to replace professional advice or live lender pricing.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Optional rate context</h3>
        <p class="muted">When a data key is configured, national mortgage survey averages (via FRED) can inform exploration screens. This is context only—not a rate lock or lender offer.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

